{
  "text": "The development of modern tracking devices and growing availability of environmental data present an opportunity: by analyzing the movement of individual animals in relation to underlying environments, inferences can be made about the movement preferences of entire populations and even species [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . While there has been a recent growing usage of track data to study animal movement in the literature, how to appropriately analyze tracks remains contentious. While friction models",
